# Generated analysis outputs — regenerable from the bigWigs + peaks + annotation
# by run_MINUTE.R, so none are committed (the .rds are tens of MB each). Only
# MINUTE_3 can run off a committed handoff; every other stage re-reads bigWigs
# anyway, so tracking the .rds bought little and cost repo size.
ChIP/results/counts/
ChIP/results/tables/
ChIP/results/figures/
ChIP/results/bed/
ChIP/results/rds/
# alternate output trees from MINUTE_RESULTS=... sensitivity runs (regenerable)
ChIP/results_*/

# Large raw inputs — downloaded from Google Drive (see ChIP/README.md), never
# committed. Peaks (ChIP/data/peaks) ARE committed. Default download targets:
ChIP/data/bigwig/
ChIP/data/annotation/
# Belt-and-suspenders in case MINUTE_DATA points somewhere else in the tree:
bigwig/
*.bw
LINE.mm39.bed
SINE.mm39.bed
LTR.mm39.bed
TAD_boundaries_mm39.bed

# stray base-R plot device output
Rplots.pdf
